al and the ceremony. Surprisingly enough, nobody stood up in anger or hatred. Nobody got up shouting pleas of detest. those who wanted to participated in the prayer, and those who didnt simply sat there in silence and showed respect for those who did participate. As hard as the government tries, they will never full banish religious practices in schools. God is too powerful and so are his believers "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="709" language="en" documentId="1709" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Zack" date="05/15/2009 10:46 AM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.forerunner.com/forerunner/X0098_Ban_on_school_prayer.html#c000600" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1709" notes="" title="Banning Prayer in Public Schools Has Led to America's Demise"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="709"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator1" isPersuasive="false" labelDetailed="P25" isGold="false" annotationBatchName="batch1-first100docs" conflictResolvingAnnotation="false"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator2" isPersuasive="false" labelDetailed="P25" isGold="false" comment="It sounds a bit like he's trying to put a positive argument, implicitly/indirectly, for &quot;prayers-in-school&quot;, yet, I think he seems to assume a neutral position on the topic that it doesn't matter if the prayers are allowed in schools or not. Or may be that it should be a choice whoever wants to participate in the prayers should be allowed to do so." annotationBatchName="batch1-first100docs" conflictResolvingAnnotation="false"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="67" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator3" isPersuasive="false" labelDetailed="P25" isGold="false" comment="just his story?" annotationBatchName="batch1-first100docs" conflictResolvingAnnotation="false"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="79" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" isPersuasive="false" isGold="true" annotationBatchName="batch1-first100docs" conflictResolvingAnnotation="false"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 55 67 79"/></xmi:XMI>